A developer writes a Minesweeper game in JavaScript. The game board is a 20×20 grid of div tiles, each with an id like 'tile_0', 'tile_1', etc., created in a loop. Mines are stored in an array `mines`. The `touchTile` function uses the following code to get neighbour IDs of a tile:

function getNeighbours(id) {
  const idx = Number(id.split('_')[1]);
  const row = Math.floor(idx / 20);
  const col = idx % 20;
  const result = [];
  for (let dr = -1; dr <= 1; dr++) {
    for (let dc = -1; dc <= 1; dc++) {
      if (dr === 0 && dc === 0) continue;
      const r = row + dr, c = col + dc;
      if (r < 0 || r >= 20 || c < 0 || c >= 20) continue;
      result.push('tile_' + (r * 20 + c));
    }
  }
  return result;
}

During a game, the player clicks on tile_0 (top-left corner). Which of the following correctly describes the behaviour of `getNeighbours('tile_0')`?

